Construct a buffer with the specified capacity.

@param capacity
           The capacity of this buffer

Answers the array that backs this buffer.
It wants to allow array-backed buffers to be passed to native code more efficiently. Subclasses provide more concrete return values for this method.
Modifications to this buffer's content will cause the returned array's content to be modified, and vice versa.
Invoking the hasArray method before invoking this method can guarantee it to be called safely.
@return The array that backs this buffer
@throws ReadOnlyBufferException - If this buffer is backed by an array but is read-only UnsupportedOperationException - If this buffer is not backed by an accessible array @since 1.6

Returns the offset within this buffer's backing array of the first element of the buffer (optional operation).
If this buffer is backed by an array then buffer position p corresponds to array index p + arrayOffset().
Invoke the hasArray method before invoking this method in order to ensure that this buffer has an accessible backing array.
@return The offset within this buffer's array of the first element of the buffer
@throws ReadOnlyBufferException - If this buffer is backed by an array but is read-only UnsupportedOperationException - If this buffer is not backed by an accessible array
@since 1.6

Answers if this buffer is backed by an available array.

If it returns true then the array and
arrayOffset methods can be called safely.

@return true if and only if this buffer is backed by an array and is
        not read-only.

@since 1.6

Answers if this buffer is direct.

@return true if and only if this buffer is direct

@since 1.6

Indicates whether this buffer is read-only.

@return {@code true} if this buffer is read-only, {@code false}
        otherwise.

