Reads all the bytes from the given input stream.

Calls read multiple times on the given input stream until it receives an
end of file marker. Returns the combined results as a byte array. Note
that this method may block if the underlying stream read blocks.

@param is
           the input stream to be read.
@return the content of the stream as a byte array.
@throws IOException
            if a read error occurs.

summary.para:
Basically this class is part of the API to the stream based ZLIB compression library and is used as such by {@code InflaterInputStream} and its descendants.
The typical usage of a {@code Inflater} outside this package consists of a specific call to one of its constructors before being passed to an instance of {@code InflaterInputStream}.
@see InflaterInputStream @see Deflater

